  "body": "## Preamble\r\n\r\n    EIP: <to be assigned>\r\n    Title: Search interface standard\r\n    Author: Vincent Stark <vince@xiveti.com>\r\n    Type: Standard Track\r\n    Category: ERC\r\n    Status: Draft\r\n    Created: 2018-01-28\r\n\r\n## Simple Summary\r\nDefine a search interface standard to be used by Ethereum search engines. This would provide a way to search for data inside smart contracts' history.\r\n\r\nEach smart contract that supports this ERC defines `search()` function:\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction search(address _addr, string _query) external view returns (result)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt takes either one of `_addr` or `_query`, or both. It returns `result` formatted in Markdown. Markdown is chosen due to the unknown structure of `result`: it can be a list, an image, a list of images, a text blob, or anything else.\r\n\r\nThe details of `search()` function implementation will be different, based on specific smart contract functionality.\r\n\r\n## Use Cases\r\nYou would ask a big **\"WHY?\"** Why do we need this standard?\r\n\r\nDApps and smart contracts are hard to discover and find. It's like Internet in 1990s. We have catalogs, directories, some references here and there, and then bookmarks for our favourite apps.\r\n\r\nWhat is needed a universal search engine that would:\r\n* Discover DApps (outside of scope of this ERC) - like crawling the Web\r\n* Search for data inside DApps - like querying a search database for data from Web pages\r\n\r\nUse cases:\r\n* *Find all the DApps that I ever transacted with.*\r\n* Find blockchains where my nickname or email has been ever mentioned.\r\n* Find transactions with a specific note in my company's ledger.\r\n* Find messages containing a specific string in Ethereum-based blog.\r\n* ...even find CryptoKitties with certain words in their name.\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/).\r\n\r\n\r\n",
